  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  History of HIV-1 infection confirmed by standard serological tests

          -  Stable medical regimen for treatment of HIV disease and associated conditions for at
             least 4 weeks prior to screening

          -  Patient-reported history of diarrhea, defined as either persistently loose stools
             despite regular ADM use, or one or more watery bowel movements per day without regular
             ADM use, of at least 1 month duration

          -  Colonoscopy within the past 5 years if â‰¥ 50 years of age.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy or breast-feeding

          -  Current or past gastrointestinal (GI) medical or surgical conditions

          -  Use of certain opiate pain medication within 2 weeks of screening

          -  Use of an antibiotic within 2 weeks prior to screening, with the exception of stable
             antibiotic therapy for prophylactic treatment of infection or an HIV-associated
             condition

          -  CD4 counts &lt; 100 cells/mm3

          -  Previous randomization into this study, or into any other crofelemer study
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
